                        <additions>
                            <list>
                                <item xml:id="e1">
                                    <desc>The manuscript was revised, corrected and completed by
                                        another hand.</desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e2">
                                    <desc type="findingAid">There are divisions on the monthly reading for the 13th of
                                        each month, the day of the saint’s feast, except for the
                                        months of Ḫǝdār and Miyāzyā: 
                                        <date ref="ethiocal:Tahsas13">13 Tāḫśāś</date> on <locus target="#3va"/>;
                                        <date ref="ethiocal:Terr13">13 Ṭǝrr</date> on <locus target="#6ra"/>;
                                        <date ref="ethiocal:Yakkatit13">13 Yakkātit</date> on <locus target="#8vb"/>;
                                        <date ref="ethiocal:Maggabit13">13 Maggābit</date> on <locus target="#11rb"/>;
                                        <date ref="ethiocal:Genbot13">13 Gǝnbot</date> on <locus target="#15vb"/>;
                                        <date ref="ethiocal:Sane13">13 Sane</date> on <locus target="#18va"/>;
                                        <date ref="ethiocal:Hamle13">13 Ḥamle</date> on <locus target="#20va"/>;
                                        <date ref="ethiocal:Nahase13">13 Naḥase</date> on <locus target="#22rb"/>;
                                        <date ref="ethiocal:Maskaram13">13 Maskaram</date> on <locus target="#23rb"/>;
                                        <date ref="ethiocal:Teqemt13">13 Ṭǝqǝmt</date> on <locus target="#25ra"/>.
                                    </desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e3">
                                    <desc>The exemplar from which this manuscript was copied must
                                        have been written at the time of the abbot <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14784TanseaK"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: PRS14784TanseaK</span></persName>, who is mentioned in a supplication on <locus target="#1vb"/>. This exemplar must be different
                                        from the manuscript used for the edition <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/KTS4953V"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1901FilposYohannes"/><title level="m">Il Gadla Filpos e il Gadla Yoḥannes di Dabra Bizan</title><title level="s">&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;Atti della Reale Accademia dei Lincei, Memorie, Classe di scienze morali, storiche e filologiche&lt;/hi&gt;</title><author><forename>Carlo</forename><surname>Conti Rossini</surname></author><pubPlace>Roma</pubPlace><publisher>Tipografia della R. Accademia dei Lincei</publisher><date>1901</date><series><title level="s">&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;Atti della Reale Accademia dei Lincei, Memorie, Classe di scienze morali, storiche e filologiche&lt;/hi&gt;</title><biblScope unit="volume">Serie quinta, 8</biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">Serie quinta, 8</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Hagiography</note><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1901FilposYohannes</note></note><note type="tag">Hagiography</note><note type="tag">bm:ContiRossini1901FilposYohannes</note></bibl>, as the two texts present minor
                                        differences.</desc>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez">በረከተ፡ ጸሎቱ፡ ይክዐው፡ ፍጡነ፡ ወያፈድፍድ፡ በላዕለ፡ <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14784TanseaK"><roleName type="title">አቡነ፡</roleName> ተንሥአ፡
                                        ክርስቶስ፡</persName> ወበላዕለ፡ ኵሎሙ፡ ደቂቀ፡ ቢዘን።.</q>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                        </additions>
                        
